cs.CR, cs.DS, cs.DC, cs.NI, cs.SE 

This paper is likely to belong to the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as it presents a new system for anonymous messaging that protects against traffic-analysis attacks and prevents anonymous denial-of-service by malicious clients. It also makes use of techniques used in systems for private information retrieval and secure multi-party computation, which are common in the field of cryptography and security. 

It could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as the system presented in the paper involves building an anonymity set of millions of users, which requires efficient data structures and algorithms. 

cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is another likely category as the paper discusses the scalability of the system to handle millions of users, which requires distributed and parallel computing techniques. 

cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also a possible category as the paper presents a messaging system that operates over a network and requires efficient communication protocols. 

Finally, cs.SE (Software Engineering) could be a relevant category as the paper presents a new system that requires software engineering techniques to design, implement, and test.
